<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 11:37PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Forsyth, northern
Davidson and northwestern Guilford Counties through 1230 AM EDT...
At 1137 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bermuda Run, or 9 miles east of Mocksville, moving northeast at 30
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, Winston-Salem, High Point, Lexington, Kernersville,
Clemmons, Bermuda Run, Lewisville, Stokesdale and Walkertown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
